<inglise> - professional requalification or training. </inglise>
<eesti> - kutsealane &uuml;mber&otilde;pe v&otilde;i v&auml;lja&otilde;pe. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The lump-sum premium shall not exceed EUR 150000 per integrated collective project. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hekordse h&uuml;vitise summa ei tohi olla &uuml;le 150 000 euro &uuml;he integreeritud &uuml;hisprojekti kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> The management authority shall determine the amount of the premium actually paid and how it is shared between the beneficiaries according to the scale of the project and the financial commitments made by each participant. </inglise>
<eesti> Korraldusasutus m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks tegelikult makstava h&uuml;vitise summa ning selle jagunemise h&uuml;vitisesaajate vahel projekti ulatuse ja iga osaleja rahaliste kohustuste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> Socioeconomic measures </inglise>
<eesti> Sotsiaal-majanduslikud meetmed </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Article, "fisherman" means anyone engaging in his main occupation on board an operational seagoing fishing vessel. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas artiklis t&auml;hendab "kalur" iga isikut, kelle p&otilde;hitegevus on seotud kasutusel oleva kalalaeva pardal toimuva tegevusega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States may take, for fishermen, measures of a socioeconomic nature associated with restructuring of the Community fisheries sector within the meaning of Article 11 of Regulation (EEC) No 3760/92. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad v&otilde;tta kalurite suhtes sotsiaal-majanduslikke meetmeid, mis on seotud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3760/92 artiklis 11 kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud &uuml;henduse kalandussektori &uuml;mberkorraldamisega. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Financial assistance from the FIFG may be granted only for the following measures: </inglise>
<eesti> FIFGi rahalist abi v&otilde;ib anda ainult j&auml;rgmistele meetmetele: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) part-financing of national early-retirement schemes for fishermen, provided that the following conditions are fulfilled: </inglise>
<eesti> a) kalurite riiklike ennet&auml;htaegse pensioni kavade osaline rahastamine, kui on t&auml;idetud j&auml;rgmised tingimused: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) at the time of early retirement, the age of the beneficiaries of the measure must be not more than 10 years from the legal retirement age within the meaning of the legislation in force in the Member State, or the beneficiaries must be aged at least 55; </inglise>
<eesti> i) ennet&auml;htaegselt pensionile j&auml;&auml;mise ajal ei tohi h&uuml;vitisesaajad olla rohkem kui k&uuml;mme aastat k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis &otilde;igusaktidega kohaldatavast ametlikust pensionieast nooremad v&otilde;i peavad olema v&auml;hemalt 55-aastased; </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) the beneficiaries can show that they have worked for at least 10 years as fishermen. </inglise>
<eesti> ii) h&uuml;vitisesaajad suudavad t&otilde;estada, et nad on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kaluritena v&auml;hemalt k&uuml;mme aastat. </eesti>
<inglise> However, contributions to the normal retirement scheme for fishermen during the period of early retirement shall not be eligible for financial assistance from the FIFG. </inglise>
<eesti> Ennet&auml;htaegse pensioni saamise ajal ei kuulu kalurite tavapensioni sissemaksed FIFGi rahalise abi alla. </eesti>
<inglise> In each Member State, for the entire programming period the number of beneficiaries may not exceed the number of jobs eliminated on board fishing vessels as a result of those vessels permanently stopping fishing activities within the meaning of Article 7; </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;heski liikmesriigis ei tohi kogu programmit&ouml;&ouml; ajal olla h&uuml;vitisesaajate arv suurem kui kalalaevadel likvideeritud ametikohtade arv, mille on tinginud nimetatud laevade l&otilde;plik k&otilde;rvaldamine p&uuml;&uuml;gitegevusest artikli 7 t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) granting individual compensatory payments to fishermen who can show that they have worked for at least twelve months as fishermen, on the basis of an eligible cost limited to EUR 10000 per individual beneficiary, provided the vessel on which the beneficiaries were employed has been the object of measures permanently stopping its activities, within the meaning of Article 7; </inglise>
<eesti> b) individuaalsed h&uuml;vitised kaluritele, kes suudavad t&otilde;endada, et nad on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kalurina v&auml;hemalt kaksteist kuud, maksimumsummas 10 000 eurot iga h&uuml;vitisesaaja kohta tingimusel, et laeva suhtes, mille pardal h&uuml;vitisesaajad t&ouml;&ouml;tasid, on kohaldatud l&otilde;pliku p&uuml;&uuml;gitegevusest k&otilde;rvaldamise meetmeid artikli 7 t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) granting non-renewable individual compensatory payments to fishermen who can show that they have worked for at least five years as fishermen, to help them retrain or diversify their activities outside maritime fisheries under an individual or collective social plan, on the basis of an eligible cost limited to EUR 50000 per individual beneficiary; the management authority shall determine the individual amount according to the scale of the retraining and diversification project and the financial commitment entered into by the beneficiary; </inglise>
<eesti> c) &uuml;hekordsed individuaalsed h&uuml;vitised kaluritele, kes suudavad t&otilde;endada, et nad on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kalurina v&auml;hemalt viis aastat, &uuml;mber&otilde;ppeks v&otilde;i oma tegevuse laiendamiseks v&auml;ljaspool merekalap&uuml;&uuml;ki individuaalse v&otilde;i &uuml;hise sotsiaalkava alusel maksimumsummas 50 000 eurot iga h&uuml;vitisesaaja kohta; korraldusasutus m&auml;&auml;rab &uuml;ksiksumma kindlaks &uuml;mber&otilde;ppe- ja laiendamisprojekti ulatuse ning h&uuml;vitisesaaja rahalise kohustuse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) granting individual premiums to fishermen younger than 3 5 years who can demonstrate that they have worked at least five years as fishermen or can demonstrate equivalent vocational training and who acquire for the first time part or total ownership in a fishing vessel, provided that the following conditions are fulfilled: </inglise>
<eesti> d) individuaalsed h&uuml;vitised alla 35 aasta vanustele kaluritele, kes t&otilde;endavad, et nad on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kalurina v&auml;hemalt viis aastat v&otilde;i et neil on v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rne kutse&otilde;ppealane ettevalmistus ning kes saavad esimest korda kalalaeva oma osalisse v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikku omandisse, kui on t&auml;idetud j&auml;rgmised tingimused: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) the fishing vessel must have an overall length between 7 and 24 metres; at the time of acquisition of ownership it must be aged between 10 and 20 years, it must be operational and it must be registered in the fishing vessel register of the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> i) kalalaeva kogupikkus peab olema 7-24 meetrit; omandi &uuml;lemineku ajal peab laeva vanus olema 10-20 aastat, laev peab olema kasutusel ning &uuml;henduse kalalaevade registrisse kantud; </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) the transfer of ownership does not occur within the same family up to the second degree. </inglise>
<eesti> ii) omandi &uuml;leminek ei toimu &uuml;he perekonna ulatuses kuni teise sugup&otilde;lveni. </eesti>
<inglise> The management authority shall determine the amount of each individual premium in particular on the basis of the size and age of the vessel and of the financial conditions of the acquisition (cost of acquisition of ownership; level and conditions of bank loan; guarantee, if any, given by a third party; and/or other financial engineering facilities). </inglise>
