<inglise> (b) where a fisheries agreement is not renewed, or where it is suspended, for the Community fleets dependent on the agreement; the granting of compensation may not last longer than six months; it may be extended by a further six months provided a conversion plan approved by the Commission is implemented for the fleet concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> b) kalanduskokkuleppest s&otilde;ltuvatele &uuml;henduse laevastikele, kui kokkulepet ei uuendata v&otilde;i kui see peatatakse; h&uuml;vitise v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata kuni kuueks kuuks; seda v&otilde;ib pikendada veel kuue kuu v&otilde;rra, kui asjaomase laevastiku suhtes rakendatakse &uuml;henduse poolt heaks kiidetud &uuml;mberkorralduskava; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) where a plan is introduced for the recovery of a resource threatened with exhaustion, decided by the Commission or by one or some Member States; the granting of compensation may last for no more than two years and may be extended by a further year. </inglise>
<eesti> c) kui komisjoni v&otilde;i &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme liikmesriigi otsuse kohaselt rakendatakse ammendumisohus olevate kalavarude taastamise kava; h&uuml;vitise v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata kuni kaheks aastaks ning pikendada veel &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise> Compensation may also be granted, subject to the same restrictions as to duration, to the processing industry where it depends for its supply on a resource covered by a recovery plan and where imports cannot compensate for the reduced supply. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitise v&otilde;ib samade kestvuspiirangutega m&auml;&auml;rata ka t&ouml;&ouml;tlevale t&ouml;&ouml;stusele, kui selle tarned s&otilde;ltuvad varudest, mille suhtes kehtib taastamiskava ning kui impordi abil ei ole v&otilde;imalik katta tarnete v&auml;henemist. </eesti>
<inglise> Before the recovery plan is put into place the management authority shall forward to the Commission suitable scientific and economic justification. </inglise>
