<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States may grant financial compensation to fishermen and owners of vessels where a Council Decision imposes technical restrictions on the use of certain gear or fishing methods; this aid is intended to cover the technical adjustment and may not be paid for more than six months. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad anda kaluritele ja laevaomanikele rahalist h&uuml;vitist, kui n&otilde;ukogu otsusega kehtestatakse tehnilised piirangud teatavate p&uuml;&uuml;givahendite v&otilde;i kalap&uuml;&uuml;giviiside kasutamise suhtes; nimetatud abi on ette n&auml;htud tehniliseks kohandamiseks ning seda v&otilde;ib maksta mitte &uuml;le kuue kuu. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The financial contribution from the FIFG to the measures referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 per Member State for the entire period from 2000 to 2006 may not exceed the higher of the following two thresholds: EUR 1 million or 4 % of the Community financial assistance allocated to the sector in the Member State concerned. </inglise>
