<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> "Pilot project" means a project carried out by an economic operator, a scientific or technical body or another competent body to test, in conditions approaching actual conditions in the industry, the technical reliability and/or financial viability of an innovative technology with a view to acquiring and disseminating technical and/or financial knowledge of the technology being tested. </inglise>
<eesti> "Katseprojekt" on ettev&otilde;tte, teadus- v&otilde;i tehnikaasutuse v&otilde;i muu p&auml;deva asutuse poolt teostatav projekt, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on katsetada t&ouml;&ouml;stusharu tegelikele tingimustele l&auml;hedastel tingimustel uuendusliku tehnoloogia tehnilist teostatavust ja/v&otilde;i rahanduslikku eluj&otilde;ulisust ning saada ja levitada katsetatava tehnoloogiaga seotud tehnilist ja/v&otilde;i rahanduslikku teavet. </eesti>
<inglise> Pilot projects shall always comprise scientific monitoring of sufficient intensity and duration to obtain significant results; they must be the subject of scientific reports forwarded to the management authority. </inglise>
<eesti> Katseprojektid h&otilde;lmavad alati usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsete tulemuste saamiseks vajaliku intensiivsuse ja kestusega teaduslikku seiret; katseprojektide kohta koostatakse teaduslikud aruanded, mis edastatakse korraldusasutusele. </eesti>
<inglise> The latter shall immediately forward such reports to the Commission for information. </inglise>
